Introduced Version
HOUSE
RESOLUTION No. ___
Introduced by: Moed, Smaltz
____________________________________
1 A HOUSE RESOLUTION memorializing Robert Hall
2 Weir.
3 Whereas, Robert Hall Weir, known professionally as Bob
4 Weir, was a founding member, guitarist, and vocalist of the
5 Grateful Dead, one of the most influential and enduring bands
6 in American music;
7 Whereas, For more than six decades, Bob Weir shaped the
8 sound of American music through his distinctive rhythm guitar
9 style, innovative songwriting, and unwavering commitment to
10 live performance;
11 Whereas, His work drew deeply from the traditions that
12 define Americana, including blues, jazz, folk, country, and rock,
13 then blended them into a uniquely American sound that
14 influenced generations of musicians and helped shape modern
20262414
HR 1531/DI 140 2026

2
1 music culture;
2 Whereas, Through his performances with the Grateful Dead,
3 RatDog, Furthur, Dead & Company, and numerous
4 collaborations, Bob Weir helped create one of the most
5 enduring music communities in American music;
6 Whereas, Bob Weir and the Grateful Dead shared a long and
7 meaningful relationship with Indiana audiences, especially
8 through their performances at the venue remembered by
9 generations of Hoosiers simply as "Deer Creek";
10 Whereas, His music fostered a sense of community,
11 connection, and joy that reached people of all ages and
12 backgrounds, leaving a cultural legacy that continues to
13 resonate deeply with Hoosiers; and
14 Whereas, Bob Weir will be greatly missed for his lifelong
15 dedication to artistic exploration, environmental stewardship,
16 and philanthropy, which was reflected in values that enrich
17 public life and strengthen the fabric of communities across the
18 country: Therefore,
19 Be it resolved by the House of Representatives of the
20 General Assembly of the State of Indiana:
21 SECTION 1. That the Indiana House of Representatives
22 honors and memorializes the life, legacy, and cultural
23 contributions of Bob Weir and extends its condolences to his
24 family, friends, and the many fans whose lives were touched by
25 his music.
26 SECTION 2. That the Principal Clerk of the House of
27 Representatives shall transmit copies of this resolution to the
28 family of Bob Weir.
